# Surgery Schedule Rebuild Walkthrough

The Surgery Schedule application has been completely rebuilt with a modern, high-performance architecture while preserving the original clinical functionality.

## New Design Highlights

### 1. "WOW" Dashboard
- **Glassmorphism UI**: Uses depth, blurs, and a deep indigo/emerald palette for a premium feel.
- **Interactive Grid**: Surgery cards feature status badges, emergency highlights, and smooth hover scales.
- **Slide-over Details**: Replaces cumbersome modals with a professional slide-in panel for patient information.

### 2. Clinical Intelligence
- **Incremental Loading**: Fetches vital signs and labs in Phase 1, then loads medications and history in Phase 2 to ensure zero UI lag.
- **Persistent Evaluation**: Anesthesia evaluation data is now saved to the server via `/api/save_eval`, allowing users to resume work across sessions.
- **Integrated PDF Engine**: Fully ports the complex coordinate mapping from the original system, producing high-fidelity PDF reports with Noto Sans font support.

## Project Structure
- [/app.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/app.py): Optimized Flask backend.
- [/templates/index.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/templates/index.html): Modern layout structure.
- [/static/css/main.css](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/static/css/main.css): Premium design system.
- [/static/js/app.js](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/static/js/app.js): Core app logic and PDF engine.
- [/legacy/](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/legacy/): **Archive of the previous design.**

## How to Verify
1.  Run `python app.py` and open `http://localhost:5000`.
2.  Search for today's surgery list.
3.  Click a surgery card to see the slide-over detail view.
4.  Fill out some evaluation form sections (they will auto-save).
5.  Click "產生評估單" to generate the professional PDF report.
